reviews.text: Beautiful place to visit. One of the best displayed Museums I've seen. Manageable size and friendly knowledgeable volunteers. You can avoid the Holocaust section.  Interesting even if not interested! Nice cafe too.

Such a brilliant museum. Gives a brief introduction to the faith. The main part of the museum gives a brilliant insight into the stories and history of Jewish people in Britain, from the Normon conquest to modern day. There is a brilliant balance between the general history and personal experiences. It taught me so much I never knew. Also visited the exhibition "Jews, Money, Myth". So, so interesting and insightful! Wonderfully curated. There was printed texts on the walls of a conversation between the director and curator, giving insight into the reasons for what was exhibited and what was not and the reasons why. I would definitely recommend.

Good insight into Jewish history. Very large section on London history some of which is good some of which is terrible (suffering, poverty) - reflected well. As to whether to immerse yourself? Wait till they have exhibition or a peculiar on So you get to see one more floor
A well appointed museum that is easy to see in 4 hours. The displays are well lit and the descriptions easily read. Well worth the visit
Nice and interesting museum full of Jewish and Israeli history and even more.  Small cafe for a quick lunch. Would recommend it as Camden Market very near by. Wish the ticket price was lower..

Best place to visit . It is found inside Addis Ababa university , College of natural and computational science compound .
Several wild animals are found reserved ( killed and dried ) 
It has entrance fee 
For regular students (AAU students ) and children - 5 birr
For adult Ethiopians - 15 birr
For foreigners - 100 birr 
If you want to record and take a picture you have to pay another fee .
But all the payments are totally worth it .
I RECOMMEND YOU TO VISIT THIS PLACE .
Museum was closed despite that it's supposed to be opened.  No explanations.  Don't bother going.
It is consist of historical and inspire objects.
Easy to miss. Still worth a walk through for the insect and mammal collections, modest though they are. Gives a sense of the biological  diversity of the country.
I am studying here nd learning........

Minus one star for being open-air (self opinion). Myself just prefers air-conditioned. Except that, this is the best food mall I ever know. It is ranged from fair class food to medium-high. So that is suit for every age range.

Dude I love this Shopping Mall this is really great and has a lot of things to see. At the source surrounded by several other Shopping Malls where you can find everything. It is definitely worth it if you spent time in bkk

Locating next to Siam BTS. The place is full of eateries. They have Chinese, Korean, Japanese, Thai etc kind of food serving restaurants. If you want to eat something it is the correct place for you. Besides the mall also has section for fashion on the lower level. Behind the mall is another walking area where you might find an interesting place to eat and stores you might want to take a look into. It's a good place to explore at night.

Good enough place, i would however recommend that a center with such a huge turn over could afford more bins, and possibly a more interesting variety than the same old stuff found at every other shopping center. Other than that, it looks good, has some interesting things for sale.

On the other side of Siam Paragon in Bangkok, Siam Square One is another shopping mall. It serves many local restaurants as well as international cuisine. The Line Village shop is also located in this mall.
